rComments: intro to social science was a bird course! i got an A in that course! i absolutely love Mackinnon, the ONLY WAY to ace that course is to do what i tell you. the focus of the exams is 80% on the lecture, so write down EVERYTHING he says, don't look at the powerpoint just write down everything he says, from random facts to statistics

I'm a science student and this was my favourite class in my 3 years at UTSC. He's HILARIOUS in a cranky kind of way and I thoroughly enjoyed his lectures. He can kind of mumble a bit, but it's not a big deal. He's actually my favourite prof.

He is my favorurite professor. I think he is one of the best professors at UTSC. I took the first year sociology course as an elective. His lectures made me love sociology and I ended up doing a minor in it. He is very fair in his exams. I learnt a lot from him. He really wants his students to do good. I wish more professors are like him.

This prof is amazing! there is only ONE RULE to get an A+ in his class, and that's righting down every single thing he says, because his exams are based on details of the lectures. If you re read all the lectures+some of the textbook, you're looking at an A!

Lectures and lecture notes will benefit you greatly, so make sure to attend as he highlights many topics and examples that are relevant and will be on the exams. He has quite a funny sarcastic humour to him. A relatively easy course. Make sure to know your definitions.

One of the better profs UTSC has. Always willing to help during office hours.  Mackinnon uses excellent examples during lectures. exams easy as long as you study/attend lectures.  Extremely intelligent man who will never talk down to anyone.  Students who have a problem with his style or personality need to examine themselves.  Prof Mack rules!
Overall a great prof. Make sure you know the meaning of all the key terms and the context in which he used them for the final. Scored A in the course.

Prof. MacKinnon is an excellent professor. I have been out of the classroom for over 20 years. Was able to score A on his final. Listen to highlighted points that he stresses, know the terms, follow his powerpoint and read book. Would be more beneficial to read book prior to class. He is an excellent prof. Thumbs up!

He was a bit boring but his jokes were pretty funny. Slides were not greatly organized. Definitely read the textbook. Exam is organized in three parts: lecture, textbook, mini textbook (forgot the names) so he will go in depth in each part. matching portion of exams will throw you off. know definitions inside out!

MacKinnon is a good lecturer, as he condenses the material to key points and explains it well. He gives solid examples and has excellent power points. I did not enjoy the controversial elements of his lectures, at points we was biased towards a particular view which were often more armchair opinions than good scientific information.

Awesome professor, exams are easy and course is interesting. But don't try to leave out the front door because he'll call you out and make you leave out the back, haha. SOCA01 and SOCA02 were the same format.

I think that he was actually quite boring. His lectures make you want to fall asleep, and I actually found that reading the textbook was more efficient than attending his lectures, despite lectures amounting to a certain percentage of exams. This can be said about Sociology Pt II as well - SOCA02H3

Mackinnon is TO unreal for words! Great prof! Makes the lecture INTERESTING, makes you laugh, his points are used on exam. Textbook use not too high, but still is relevant.Exam is very fair. Epic professor.

I LOVED LOVED LOVED THIS PROF! I passed his class with a solid A, and all I did was simply memorize my lecture notes and skim the readings from the textbook. His examples are hillarious, and he has a little swag about him. The course's content is very interesting, and he does a great job teaching it.

One of my favourite profs. keeps the lectures interesting, cuts down the readings near midterms and finals. He looks really serious and intimidating, but hes really funny. The exams arent too bad. no assignments just 2 exams all multiple choice and matching. he doesnt try to trick you so i thought they were alright. Awesome prof!

Great prof! Very interesting. knows his stuff. Very personable. Made me change my subject post, i loved the content immensely! Pay attention to his LEC's and you'll be good.. skim the chapters.. and reading.. and your guaranteed an 85%

I thought he was going to be a horrible prof because he talks really slow but he was actually very good ! His slow pace helped when I was taking notes and he can be really funny ! Class is super easy if you attend all the lectures, overall I really enjoyed the class and prof ! Time slot in the evening was good too !

He is a good professor. He knows what he is talking about and that in itself is helpful. This isn?t a bird course but you really shouldn?t be hoping for bird courses in University. His examples are relevant and sometimes quite funny, as long as you apply yourself this course won?t harm you.

Slackest course imaginable, the easiest A I've ever gotten. No assignments, just multiple choice and matching questions on two exams. I don't understand how anyone could ever find this class difficult.

hes a good prof!all those who're she midterm saying that the midterm was hard should GO TO HIS LECTURES!the books are almost useless in this course. u need to know what he says in the lecture and have an idea of what the chapters are about..i barely studied and got an A in this course!
Best prof ever !
All of you who are complaining about the midterm ; do not worry, I took this course in the summer and the midterm is a disaster but he makes his final UNBELIEVABLY easy.

You know the class average was gonna be low when you opened the first page of the midterm and the whole gym collectively groaned with you. IT WAS HORRIBLE! I attended every lecture, did the readings and it was still not enough. You literally need to have a photographic memory to pass this course. Don't know where those questions came from...

Initially went into this course with interest and when he started to lecture for 3 hours I slowly began to disconnect. He seems like a very kind man but his midterm was BRUTAL! Honestly no amount of studying could have prepared me for it because it was not reflective of what was taught
i love him

Mackinnon does have a tendency to repeat himself but overall I found his lectures to be interesting. It's all about knowing how to study in this course because you have to read the textbook, whatever he says in lecture, and the additional readings assigned to get a guaranteed A+. Also he bellcurves up a lot and the exams aren't cumulative.

Totally regret taking this course. Lectures were 3 hours straight and extremely disorganized. Has a habit of repeating the same things over and over again. Attn Future Students: Do not take this course thinking it's a bird course, you will be sorry when your mark is nowhere near as high as you expected!

He is without a doubt the most boring and dull prof. at UTSC, talk about monotone and lack of enthusiasm. He is unclear, and uses irrelevant examples, he also goes way off topic.Very disorganised. On the bright side, he can sometimes be funny, and does try to help if you seek help. Also his exams are on the easier side.

Horrible lecturer!!! Class was 3 hours straight and it was death trying to listen to what he was saying. His multiple choice is ok but matching questions were impossible. Lectures were EXTREMELY disorganized and powerpoints were useless. Do not take this course thinking it is a bird course!
A good prof, easier than people say he is. His lectures are full of detail and gives many examples.
A good prof, easier than people say he is. His lectures are full of detail and gives many examples.
A very good professor. Exams are fair and easy if you study and take notes in his class.

Lectures are really just a disorganized speech but exams are straightforward and if you come to lectures and do the readings, guaranteed best mark you'll get in first year. Claims second hand smoke is not hazardous at all...

Pretty easy class as long as you do the readings and have the lecture notes. If someone you know has lecture notes, then theres no point in going to class. Matching is probably the only tough part, because its totally random. Pretty interesting class overall.

Great guy, not as boring as everyone says he is. ask him about global warming lol. once you know his style of testing, this course is very easy to get an A. read the text a bunch of times, cuz his multiple choice asks random questions not the bolded terms/definitions, and if you know his lecture slides, matching and MC/essay will be really easy.

At first, i thought he was so boring but he turned out to be VERY interesting. I learned a lot in his class. YOU MUST Attend lectures b/c 40% of the exams based on them. The fact that he talks slow and repeats important points helps if you tend to daydream:P...or would it be evening dream:S hmmm
At first I thought he was very boring, but after a couple lectures, I really like his lecture style. The exams are a  LOT harder than you would expect them to be. It is NOT a bird course
Good prof overall

He's pretty easy once you know his ways.  Pay attention to lectures and veiw the powerpoint before class.  His exams are easy, just a lot of memorizing silly stuff.  He's just very monotone and it was hard to pay attention.  I get the impression that he's just a lonely guy.

This prof is a cool character. His exams are fair and by that I mean do your readings, well heck, we didn't read and pulled a 70. But we got used his exams. Its 40 MCQS, 20 matching and one essay where you can **** it if u know anything relavent he said in the class. And you do remember his teachings cuz there are day to day life teachings.
the course isn't bad..he's a great prof and i would love to take another course with him..the course isn't hard or easy, but one can definitely do well by working hard during exam time

His exams are fair. The essay portion is based on his lectures, but there were only 4 lectures to study per exam so it wasn't bad. Just memorize the lectures and you're set! His lectures were enjoyable, he's a funny guy. I would take a course with him again.

his exams are completely messed up....his testing on lecture material is screwed up it represents so much of the mark yet there is so little to say about it...i hate the format of his exams...he's a very funny guy though....doesnt like to attend to students' questions.

He is easy to listen to and take notes from, however his grading format is flawed.  First exam is worth 40%, and the essay portion of that exam is worth 60%, yet the essay was only based on 1% of the lecture notes?  I studied EVERYTHING, but nothing was on the exam.  Hope this helps!

He is unorganized in some sense, however he's not boring, he makes you understand things. However I think he's hot headed and has too much ego, he thinks he's too smart for everyone. I approaced him once, he was rude, and called me with the index finger, he has a problem saying sorry when he's mistaken!!!
He's a really interesting prof but he doesnt like to answer questions.

He taught me many years ago and he is the only prof I learned anything from.He is helpful intelligent and made learning interesting/authentic.He motivates you to continue your education-he always told me to pursue my Masters and I did thanks to him!He goes above and beyond and is in my opinion the best prof out there!I took any class he taught ES

not very helpful, if you ask him a question he seems rather uninterested and annoyed. i did like his sense of humour. he goes off topic sometimes and doesn't make a good enough effort to explain class syllabus. he just appears mean but his lectures were ok. the matching on exams are hard, the MC is easy if you study and the essay is marked fairly.
A class i actually looked forward to going and miss. Very interesting class and a good prof! keeps your attention and I can honestly say I was never bored or sleepy in that class!
Great class, very interesting material.  Slow-paced so that everyone can understand, but not to a point where it's boring.
likes to ramble, gets off topic and talks to himself a lot.

he WILL make you feel stupid when you try to talk to him, and his lectures can be boring...but if you stick with it and study hard, his exams are fair and you should do well. a lot of people don't like him because he comes off as boring and mean, but he explains concepts well in lectures. JUST MAKE SURE YOU TAKE NOTES AND STUDY. slackers stay away!

smart. fair. interesting. knows what he is talking about. essay questions on exams are based on lectures.  his lectures can be un-orangized, in the sense that he flys back and forth from different slides without any particular orders. if you pay attention to lectures then you'll do fine. great course/prof. i would recommened him.

Great prof! I made it a point to only take the Socio courses when he taught them. He's funny, though politically incorrect(which is why he's funny) presents the information in an easy to understand way & he really makes u think about what he's teaching. If u don't listen to him u won't get his style & u'll do bad on tests/exams. Use his slides! :)
He's my fave Prof ever!!! He may be dry, but he makes the material easy to understand. Hes also a very nice & kind man. His exams are so easy too. The best mark I ever got!
so boring! I'm suprised he can stand his own mumbling for two hours on tuesday night. But then again, as I always say... "vive la difference" (insert dry, corny laugh here)
He is a very kind professor.

A good professor. I had no trouble following the lectures. You really need to use the slides though. His exams were fair, but you have to study really hard. Provides a good overview of sociology, even if the prof is politically incorrect :)
His marking scheme for these two courses are mid-term 40% and final 60%. Which is tough. The final is very important. His essays are based on lectures.
i think that even though mackinnon is a hard prof, he's very nice b/c once i took his class in the summer...he gave everybody a couple of bonus points b/c he said it was his birthday..

He's a smart and interesting prof. the lectures never dull b/c he has such a gr8 sense of humor He repeats pt's that r important&uses alot of examples when explaining concepts which makes it helpful in studying for tests.da only thing he has 2 fix is his friendliness. NOT APPROACHABLE AT ALL!
Interesting course, interesting prof. Learnt a lot from him. But intensive readings... and if you wanna get good mark, remember not to skip class.

I really liked the lectures, he is funny (I am old maybe that is why I find him humerous) I did well on the exam only because I studied ALOT! He covers ALL material on the exams. Some of the workbook questions WERE really specific. The essay question was marked tough. He bell curved the grades.

forget about taking this course if this boring, wierd man is teaching it, just do not bother, please trust me you will regret it.  if you intend on taking it you might as well listen to static on a radio with spuradic screeches
